{
  "__fixture__": {
    "name": "non_replayable_raw_byte_dependent",
    "scenario": "A composer turn whose behavior depended on a user-supplied file the user pasted inline. The contract never retained the raw bytes (raw_user_supplied_text is never captured by design); the user did not re-offer the file and the evidence-driven reviewer cannot reconstruct the original input. The assembly, evidence packet, receipts, and every other capture axis remain retained; the attachment set is captured reference-only, but the user-supplied-text capture class is marked required_omitted_with_disclosure with raw_user_supplied_text_forbidden_unless_separately_retained. Replay grade resolves to non_replayable_raw_byte_dependent; the packet preserves evidence honesty — what is known, what was omitted, and why. The audit-storage manifest lists the retained artifacts and an audit-event stream; no conversation-history rows are emitted because the raw user-supplied text was never stored.",
    "exercised_contract_sections": [
      "replay_grade",
      "capture_class",
